Steps.Description:
Reads Teamcenter StructureVersion Data.
Input is not needed in workflow execution, because a TcData array already exists. Otherwise it retrieves the TcData array using information from the "TCObjectData" data element.
Steps.Name: Read TC StructureVersion

Items.Name: TransferType
Items.Description: GENOBJ, GENBOM, MM, ... The specific type of the transfer.

Items.Name: TargetTypeName
Items.Description: The TargetTypeName of the transfer (as used in preferences). This is only useful for the generic TransferTypes. It defaults to the value provided during step generation.

Items.Name: ProductKey
Items.Description: The AIG product name (e.g. T4S, T4EA, ...). It defaults to the value provided during step generation.

Items.Name: object_tag
Items.Description: The hexed PUID of the Teamcenter object to retrieve. It defaults to the value provided during step generation.

Items.Name: BomLineTargetTypeName
Items.Description:
Only if the TransferType is "GENBOM" then this parameter is required and the object
    is assumed to be an item revision with a "view" BVR. If such a BVR does not exist, 
    then no TcData will be created and no error will be thrown (empty BOM).
    It defaults to the value provided during step generation.
